<TITLE> Two die, 12 hurt in Kashmir grenade blast </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 SRINAGAR, India, Aug 13 (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - Suspected separatist militants in Kashmir killed two civilians and wounded a dozen others in a grenade attack on Monday, police said, two days ahead of India's 60th independence day anniversary. The attack took place in Bandipur town, around 65 km (40 miles) north of Srinagar, Indian Kashmir's summer capital. "The grenade was aimed at security forces but it missed the target, and exploded on the road," a police official said. No militant group has claimed responsibility for the attack. Officials say more than 42,000 people have been killed in violence in the Muslim-majority region since 1989 in a separatist revolt against Indian rule, but human rights groups put the toll at around 60,000 dead or missi
